                            <comment id="12688660" author="rnewson" created="Tue, 24 Mar 2009 12:14:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI: In my project (couchdb-lucene) I&apos;ve pulled in the ngram-based LanguageIdentifier from Nutch 0.9. Since it&apos;s Apache 2 licensed, it might be something worth integrating with Tika directly?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12702953" author="jukkaz" created="Mon, 27 Apr 2009 00:01:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The getConfidence() method in CharsetMatch is for the confidence level of the character encoding detection, not of the language detection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure if ICU4J has an easy way to determine the confidence level of language detection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Robert: Do you know how the LanguageIdentifier stuff differs from the stuff in ICU4J?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12702962" author="rnewson" created="Mon, 27 Apr 2009 00:37:09 +0100"  >
&lt;p&gt;Yes, it analyzes the frequencies of the ngrams and compares them to the ngram profiles that it packages.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12711326" author="jukkaz" created="Wed, 20 May 2009 21:36:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think something like that would be interesting for Tika. Would you like to contribute a patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12711333" author="rnewson" created="Wed, 20 May 2009 21:46:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure thing. I adapted the Nutch code for my project, it should be straightforward to do the same for Tika. It&apos;s all Apache licensed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;ll be a few days, swamped with other stuff.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12731621" author="tdunning" created="Wed, 15 Jul 2009 19:48:49 +0100"  >
&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t looked at the nutch code in forever, but my memory is that it didn&apos;t use the best statistics for the task.  Here is an approach that seems to be more accurate:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/summary?doi=10.1.1.48.1958&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/summary?doi=10.1.1.48.1958&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sadly, I don&apos;t have a Java implementation of this handy.  I can give out an ancient C implementation.&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
                            <comment id="12732130" author="jukkaz" created="Thu, 16 Jul 2009 21:14:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Anything would be fine. I&apos;m sure we can find someone to port the code to Java.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12733063" author="jukkaz" created="Sun, 19 Jul 2009 21:50:14 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I gave a look at the Nutch LanguageIdentifier code. It&apos;s indeed something we could use without too much effort.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12733092" author="chrismattmann" created="Mon, 20 Jul 2009 00:37:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey Guys:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Awesome &amp;#8211; that was the intention for Tika from the beginning &amp;#8211; Jerome and I originally proposed this as a downstream feature and I think that the time has come.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Chris&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12737368" author="chrismattmann" created="Fri, 31 Jul 2009 00:59:15 +0100"  >&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;set component and fix version&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12774553" author="jukkaz" created="Sat, 7 Nov 2009 04:34:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have refactored and simplified the language identifier code to better meet the needs of Tika. Most notably I fixed the ngram length to three characters to reduce the size of the language profile files and to make the ngram classes simpler.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AutoDetectParser now automatically attempts to detect the document language and sets the Metadata.LANGUAGE property if a reasonably certain language profile match is found.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12777959" author="chrismattmann" created="Sat, 14 Nov 2009 16:26:29 +0000"  >&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;jukka fixed this, so assign goes to him&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
